        "text": "21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the ark, wherein",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the covenant of the Lord",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] It has just been said (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 8:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") that only the two tables of stone were in the ark. They must then be meant by ‘the covenant of the Lord,’ and this is borne out by such passages as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 4:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 29:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the covenant alluded to forms a part of the ten commandments. But ‘the book of the covenant’ (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 24:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") appears to have included all the laws contained in Exodus 20-23.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
